# Refactoring Guidelines

## Before Refactoring

1. Ensure `npm run build` passes on current code
2. Understand the component's responsibilities
3. Identify dependencies (props, imports, global state)

## Component Extraction

When extracting a reusable component:

### Step 1: Identify the Pattern

Find repeated markup or logic that can be abstracted.

### Step 2: Create New Component

```astro
---
// src/components/NewComponent.astro
interface Props {
  title: string;
  items: { name: string; url: string }[];
}

const { title, items } = Astro.props;
---

<div class="new-component">
  <h2>{title}</h2>
  <ul>
    {items.map((item) => (
      <li><a href={item.url}>{item.name}</a></li>
    ))}
  </ul>
</div>
```

### Step 3: Replace Original Usage

```astro
// Before
<div class="new-component">
  <h2>Projects</h2>
  <ul>...</ul>
</div>

// After
<NewComponent title="Projects" items={projects} />
```

### Step 4: Verify

Run `npm run build` to ensure types are correct.

## Moving Files

When moving files:

1. Update all import paths that reference the file
2. Update documentation if file paths are mentioned
3. Check for path alias usage (`@/`)

## Renaming

When renaming:

1. Use IDE rename feature (F2) for symbols
2. Update all string references (e.g., component names in templates)
3. Update docs and comments

## Content Schema Changes

When modifying `src/content/config.ts`:

1. Update the Zod schema
2. Run `npm run build` to catch validation errors
3. Update existing content files to match new schema
4. Update docs if the schema is documented

## Safety Checks

After refactoring:

- [ ] `npm run build` passes with 0 errors
- [ ] `astro check` reports 0 errors and 0 warnings
- [ ] Visual spot-check in `npm run preview`
- [ ] Documentation is updated if needed
